.docname {BakingRL Host Documentation}
.docauthor {BakingRL}
.include {docs}
.doclang {en}

BakingRL is the desktop host for Rocket League telemetry and plugin runtimes.
It connects to local telemetry, manages packages, enforces runtime boundaries,
opens plugin-declared webviews, and exposes host-mediated runtime APIs.

This documentation explains host behavior. Plugin authoring details belong in
the `BakingRLSDK` documentation.

## Start Here

- [Overview](pages/overview.qd): what the host does and where responsibilities
  are split.
- [Setup](pages/setup.qd): local requirements and development commands.
- [Repository Layout](pages/repository-layout.qd): how the sibling repositories
  fit together.
- [Architecture](pages/architecture.qd): host process, frontend, runtime, and
  data flow.
- [Plugin System](pages/plugin-system.qd): how packages are discovered,
  described, enabled, and mounted by the host.
- [Marketplace](pages/marketplace.qd): catalogue verification, publisher trust,
  dependency plans, and transactional installation.
- [Broadcast Workflow](pages/broadcast-workflow.qd): how the first-party stats,
  layout, visual, overlay, and OBS plugins fit together.
- [Troubleshooting](pages/troubleshooting.qd): common runtime, telemetry, and
  package-manager failures.

## Source Of Truth

Use the split below when deciding where a behavior should be documented:

```txt
BakingRL/         Host application and runtime behavior
BakingRLSDK/      SDK contracts, generator, CLI, plugin-author docs
BakingRLPlugins/  First-party and experimental plugin packages
BakingRLMarketplace/  Signed public catalogue and review metadata
```

The current host runtime API is `2.4.0`. Compatible packages declare top-level
`bakingrlApi` in the supported `2.3.x` through `2.4.x` range. Runtime API 2.2 is not supported.
